    • getLinearArrayIndex

      protected static int getLinearArrayIndex(int[] memberIndex, int[] arrayIndex)
      Get the linear index of an array member within the array. The linear index is the position that the array member would occupy in a single dimension array created by 'flattening' the original multi-dimensional array. For an array with overall dimensions of [2][3][2] the array indices and corresponding linear indices are: Array Index Linear Index [0][0][0] 0 [0][0][1] 1 [0][1][0] 2 [0][1][1] 3 [0][2][0] 4 [0][2][1] 5 [1][0][0] 6 [1][0][1] 7 [1][1][0] 8 [1][1][1] 9 [1][2][0] 10 [1][2][1] 11
      Parameters:
      memberIndex - Array of the member variable's dimension(s)
      arrayIndex - Array of the overall array dimension(s)
      Returns:
      The linear index of the array member within the array

    • compareTo

      protected static int compareTo(String arrayVariable1, String arrayVariable2)
      Compare two array variable members by array dimension value(s)
      Parameters:
      arrayVariable1 - First array variable member to compare
      arrayVariable2 - Second array variable member to compare
      Returns:
      0 if the array members are the same, -1 if the first array member occurs prior to the second array member (based the their array dimension value(s), and 1 if the first array member occurs after the second array member
